 UKIP's Nigel Farage leads pro-Brexit flotilla stunt up Thames On Air
Nigel Farage, the leader of the UK Independence Party (UKIP), is leading a flotilla of fishing trawlers up the Thames in a stunt to call for the UK's withdrawal from the EU before the referendum on June 23. The flotilla of at least 35 boats is organized by Scottish skippers, who set up the pro-Brexit Fishing for Leave campaign several weeks ago.

 The shooters male classmate says Omar asked him out
Palm Beach Post - Staff Writers
A former classmate of Omar Mateen's 2006 police academy class said he believed Mateen was gay, saying Mateen once asked him out.

 Police Account of Decisions Made During Orlando Rampage Contains Crucial Gaps
NY Times - Timothy Williams and Michael Wilson
Scores of people were already lying dead or injured inside a crowded Orlando nightclub, and the police had spent hours trying to connect with the gunman and end the situation without further violence. But when Omar Mateen threatened to set off explosives, the police decided to act, and pushed their way through a wall to end the bloody standoff.

 FL Killer visited gay club dozen times
Orlando Sentinel - Staff Writers
At least four regular customers at the Orlando gay nightclub where a gunman killed 49 people said Monday that they had seen Omar Mateen there before.

 Victims in Orland laying Dead to Stay Alive!
NY Times - Jack Healy and Marc Santora
As the sound of gunfire in the nightclub grew louder, a patron named Orlando and a female friend took cover in a cramped bathroom stall, contorting their bodies on top of the toilet so their feet could not be seen. The gunman burst into the bathroom, went straight to the stall next to them and shot the people inside.

 Mainstream Muslim Culture The Problem
CBS News - Rich Zeoli
In the wake of the tragic shooting at a club in Orlando this weekend, Milo Yiannopoulos says Islam, not just extremists groups and terrorists, but the entire religion is responsible for violence against gay people and women.
